Interface IViewRegisteredCamps

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StudentRegisteredCampsViewer
    public interface IViewRegisteredCamps
    Represents an interface that allows a student to interact with the associated registration database to print the details of all his registered camps.

    2023-11-17
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:

    • Method Detail

      • viewRegisteredCamps

        void viewRegisteredCamps​(Student student,
                         ISortCamps iSortCamps,
                         IFilterCamps iFilterCamps,
                         String filterString)
        Prints out the details of all the camps that a student has registered for. The implementor should utilise the sorting, filtering interfaces in the parameters to sort and filter the camps accordingly before printing out the camps for the student to view.
        Parameters:
        student - The student who wants to view all the camps he has registered for.
        iSortCamps - The sorting interface that can be used to sort the camps in the camp database.
        iFilterCamps - The filtering interface that can be used to filter the camps in the camp database.
        filterString - The filter string that should be used with the filtering interface to filter the camps.
